handler-abstractworker-onerror.name: onerror
handler-abstractworker-onerror.summary: The AbstractWorker.onerror property of the AbstractWorker interface represents an EventHandler, that is a function to be called when the error event occurs and bubbles through the Worker.
handler-abstractworker-onerror.title: AbstractWorker.onerror

abstractworker.name: AbstractWorker
abstractworker.summary: The AbstractWorker interface of the Web Workers API is an abstract interface that defines properties and methods that are common to all types of worker, including not only the basic Worker, but also ServiceWorker and SharedWorker.
abstractworker.title: AbstractWorker

dom-audiotrack-enabled.name: enabled
dom-audiotrack-enabled.summary: The AudioTrack property enabled specifies whether or not the described audio track is currently enabled for use. If the track is disabled by setting enabled to false, the track is muted and does not produce audio.
dom-audiotrack-enabled.title: AudioTrack.enabled

dom-audiotrack-id.name: id
dom-audiotrack-id.summary: The id property contains a string which uniquely identifies the track represented by the AudioTrack.
dom-audiotrack-id.title: AudioTrack.id

dom-audiotrack-kind.name: kind
dom-audiotrack-kind.summary: The kind property contains a string indicating the category of audio contained in the AudioTrack.
dom-audiotrack-kind.title: AudioTrack.kind

dom-audiotrack-label.name: label
dom-audiotrack-label.summary: The read-only AudioTrack property label returns a string specifying the audio track's human-readable label, if one is available; otherwise, it returns an empty string.
dom-audiotrack-label.title: AudioTrack.label

dom-audiotrack-language.name: language
dom-audiotrack-language.summary: The read-only AudioTrack property language returns a string identifying the language used in the audio track.
dom-audiotrack-language.title: AudioTrack.language

audiotrack.name: AudioTrack
audiotrack.summary: The AudioTrack interface represents a single audio track from one of the HTML media elements, <audio> or <video>.
audiotrack.title: AudioTrack

event-media-addtrack.name: addtrack_event
event-media-addtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a track is added to an AudioTrackList.
event-media-addtrack.title: AudioTrackList: addtrack event

event-media-addtrack.name: addTrack_event
event-media-addtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a track is added to a TextTrackList.
event-media-addtrack.title: TextTrackList: addtrack event

event-media-addtrack.name: addtrack_event
event-media-addtrack.summary: The addtrack event is fired when a track is added to a VideoTrackList.
event-media-addtrack.title: VideoTrackList: addtrack event

event-media-change.name: change_event
event-media-change.summary: The change event is fired when an audio track is enabled or disabled, for example by changing the track's enabled property.
event-media-change.title: AudioTrackList: change event

event-media-change.name: change_event
event-media-change.summary: The change event is fired when a text track is made active or inactive, or a textTrackList is otherwise changed.
event-media-change.title: TextTrackList: change event

event-media-change.name: change_event
event-media-change.summary: The change event is fired when a video track is made active or inactive, for example by changing the track's selected property.
event-media-change.title: VideoTrackList: change event

dom-audiotracklist-gettrackbyid.name: getTrackById
dom-audiotracklist-gettrackbyid.summary: The AudioTrackList method getTrackById() returns the first AudioTrack object from the track list whose id matches the specified string.
dom-audiotracklist-gettrackbyid.title: AudioTrackList.getTrackById()

dom-audiotracklist-length.name: length
dom-audiotracklist-length.summary: The read-only AudioTrackList property length returns the number of entries in the AudioTrackList, each of which is an AudioTrack representing one audio track in the media element.
dom-audiotracklist-length.title: AudioTrackList.length

handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.name: onaddtrack
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.summary: The AudioTrackList property onaddtrack is an event handler which is called when the addtrack event occurs, indicating that a new audio track has been added to the media element whose audio tracks the AudioTrackList represents.
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.title: AudioTrackList.onaddtrack

handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.name: onaddtrack
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.summary: The VideoTrackList property onaddtrack is an event handler which is called when the addtrack event occurs, indicating that a new video track has been added to the media element whose video tracks the VideoTrackList represents.
handler-tracklist-onaddtrack.title: VideoTrackList.onaddtrack

handler-tracklist-onchange.name: onchange
handler-tracklist-onchange.summary: The AudioTrackList property onchange is an event handler which is called when the change event occurs, indicating that one or more of the AudioTracks in the AudioTrackList have been enabled or disabled.
handler-tracklist-onchange.title: AudioTrackList.onchange

handler-tracklist-onchange.name: onchange
handler-tracklist-onchange.summary: The VideoTrackList property onchange is an event handler which is called when the change event occurs, indicating that a VideoTrack in the VideoTrackList has been made active.
handler-tracklist-onchange.title: VideoTrackList.onchange

handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.name: onremovetrack
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.summary: The AudioTrackList onremovetrack event handler is called when the removetrack event occurs, indicating that an audio track has been removed from the media element, and therefore also from the AudioTrackList.
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.title: AudioTrackList.onremovetrack

handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.name: onremovetrack
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.summary: The VideoTrackList onremovetrack event handler is called when the removetrack event occurs, indicating that a video track has been removed from the media element, and therefore also from the VideoTrackList.
handler-tracklist-onremovetrack.title: VideoTrackList.onremovetrack

event-media-removetrack.name: removetrack_event
event-media-removetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a track is removed from an AudioTrackList.
event-media-removetrack.title: AudioTrackList: removetrack event

event-media-removetrack.name: removeTrack_event
event-media-removetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a track is removed from a TextTrackList.
event-media-removetrack.title: TextTrackList: removeTrack event

event-media-removetrack.name: removetrack_event
event-media-removetrack.summary: The removetrack event is fired when a track is removed from a VideoTrackList.
event-media-removetrack.title: VideoTrackList: removetrack event

audiotracklist.name: AudioTrackList
audiotracklist.summary: The AudioTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the audio tracks contained within a given HTML media element, with each track represented by a separate AudioTrack object in the list.
audiotracklist.title: AudioTrackList

the-beforeunloadevent-interface.name: BeforeUnloadEvent
the-beforeunloadevent-interface.summary: The beforeunload event is fired when the window, the document and its resources are about to be unloaded.
the-beforeunloadevent-interface.title: BeforeUnloadEvent

dom-broadcastchannel.name: BroadcastChannel
dom-broadcastchannel.summary: The BroadcastChannel() constructor creates a new BroadcastChannel and connects it to the underlying channel.
dom-broadcastchannel.title: BroadcastChannel()

dom-broadcastchannel-close.name: close
dom-broadcastchannel-close.summary: The BroadcastChannel.close() terminates the connection to the underlying channel, allowing the object to be garbage collected. This is a necessary step to perform as there is no other way for a browser to know that this channel is not needed anymore.
dom-broadcastchannel-close.title: BroadcastChannel.close()

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a BroadcastChannel object when a message arrives on that channel.
event-message.title: BroadcastChannel: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object when the worker receives a message from its parent (i.e. when the parent sends a message using Worker.postMessage()).
event-message.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event of the EventSource API is fired when data is received through an event source.
event-message.title: EventSource: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a MessagePort object when a message arrives on that channel.

nodejs.notes: Supports the event, but only via Node EventEmitter.

event-message.title: MessagePort: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired when data is received through a WebSocket.
event-message.title: WebSocket: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a Window object when the window receives a message, for example from a call to Window.postMessage() from another browsing context.
event-message.title: Window: message event

event-message.name: message_event
event-message.summary: The message event is fired on a Worker object when the worker's parent receives a message from its worker (i.e. when the worker sends a message using DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.postMessage()).

nodejs.notes: Supports the event, but only via Node EventEmitter.

event-message.title: Worker: message event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a BroadcastChannel object when a message arrives on the channel that can't be deserialized.
event-messageerror.title: BroadcastChannel: messageerror event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.
event-messageerror.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: messageerror event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a MessagePort object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.
event-messageerror.title: MessagePort: messageerror event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a Window object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.
event-messageerror.title: Window: messageerror event

event-messageerror.name: messageerror_event
event-messageerror.summary: The messageerror event is fired on a Worker object when it receives a message that can't be deserialized.
event-messageerror.title: Worker: messageerror event

dom-broadcastchannel-name.name: name
dom-broadcastchannel-name.summary: The read-only BroadcastChannel.name property returns a DOMString, which uniquely identifies the given channel with its name. This name is passed to the BroadcastChannel() constructor at creation time and is therefore read-only.
dom-broadcastchannel-name.title: BroadcastChannel.name

handler-broadcastchannel-onmessage.name: onmessage
handler-broadcastchannel-onmessage.summary: The BroadcastChannel.onmessage event handler is a property that specifies the function to execute when a message event, of type MessageEvent, is received by this BroadcastChannel. Such an event is sent by the browser with a message broadcasted to the channel.
handler-broadcastchannel-onmessage.title: BroadcastChannel.onmessage

handler-broadcastchannel-onmessageerror.name: onmessageerror
handler-broadcastchannel-onmessageerror.summary: The onmessageerror event handler of the BroadcastChannel interface is an EventListener, called whenever an MessageEvent of type messageerror is fired on the BroadcastChannel instance  that is, when it receives a message that cannot be deserialized.
handler-broadcastchannel-onmessageerror.title: BroadcastChannel.onmessageerror

dom-broadcastchannel-postmessage.name: postMessage
dom-broadcastchannel-postmessage.summary: The BroadcastChannel.postMessage() sends a message, which can be of any kind of Object, to each listener in any browsing context with the same origin. The message is transmitted as a message event targeted at each BroadcastChannel bound to the channel.
dom-broadcastchannel-postmessage.title: BroadcastChannel.postMessage()

broadcastchannel.name: BroadcastChannel
broadcastchannel.summary: The BroadcastChannel interface represents a named channel that any browsing context of a given origin can subscribe to. It allows communication between different documents (in different windows, tabs, frames or iframes) of the same origin. Messages are broadcasted via a message event fired at all BroadcastChannel objects listening to the channel.
broadcastchannel.title: BroadcastChannel

dom-canvasgradient-addcolorstop.name: addColorStop
dom-canvasgradient-addcolorstop.summary: The CanvasGradient.addColorStop() method adds a new color stop, defined by an offset and a color, to a given canvas gradient.
dom-canvasgradient-addcolorstop.title: CanvasGradient.addColorStop()

canvasgradient.name: CanvasGradient
canvasgradient.summary: The CanvasGradient interface represents an opaque object describing a gradient. It is returned by the methods CanvasRenderingContext2D.createLinearGradient() or CanvasRenderingContext2D.createRadialGradient().

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 5.0, specifying non-finite values when adding color stops through a call to addColorStop() incorrectly throws SYNTAX_ERR instead of INDEX_SIZE_ERR.

canvasgradient.title: CanvasGradient

dom-canvaspattern-settransform.name: setTransform
dom-canvaspattern-settransform.summary: The CanvasPattern.setTransform() method uses an SVGMatrix or DOMMatrix object as the pattern's transformation matrix and invokes it on the pattern.
dom-canvaspattern-settransform.title: CanvasPattern.setTransform()

canvaspattern.name: CanvasPattern
canvaspattern.summary: The CanvasPattern interface represents an opaque object describing a pattern, based on an image, a canvas, or a video, created by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.createPattern() method.
canvaspattern.title: CanvasPattern

dom-context-2d-arc.name: arc
dom-context-2d-arc.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.arc() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a circular arc to the current sub-path.
dom-context-2d-arc.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.arc()

dom-context-2d-arcto.name: arcTo
dom-context-2d-arcto.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.arcTo() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a circular arc to the current sub-path, using the given control points and radius. The arc is automatically connected to the path's latest point with a straight line, if necessary for the specified parameters.
dom-context-2d-arcto.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.arcTo()

dom-context-2d-beginpath.name: beginPath
dom-context-2d-beginpath.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.beginPath() method of the Canvas 2D API starts a new path by emptying the list of sub-paths. Call this method when you want to create a new path.
dom-context-2d-beginpath.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.beginPath()

dom-context-2d-beziercurveto.name: bezierCurveTo
dom-context-2d-beziercurveto.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.bezierCurveTo() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a cubic Bzier curve to the current sub-path. It requires three points: the first two are control points and the third one is the end point. The starting point is the latest point in the current path, which can be changed using moveTo() before creating the Bzier curve.
dom-context-2d-beziercurveto.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.bezierCurveTo()

dom-context-2d-canvas.name: canvas
dom-context-2d-canvas.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.canvas property, part of the Canvas API, is a read-only reference to the HTMLCanvasElement object that is associated with a given context. It might be null if there is no associated <canvas> element.
dom-context-2d-canvas.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.canvas

dom-context-2d-clearrect.name: clearRect
dom-context-2d-clearrect.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.clearRect() method of the Canvas 2D API erases the pixels in a rectangular area by setting them to transparent black.
dom-context-2d-clearrect.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.clearRect()

dom-context-2d-clip.name: clip
dom-context-2d-clip.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.clip() method of the Canvas 2D API turns the current or given path into the current clipping region. The previous clipping region, if any, is intersected with the current or given path to create the new clipping region.
dom-context-2d-clip.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.clip()

dom-context-2d-closepath.name: closePath
dom-context-2d-closepath.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.closePath() method of the Canvas 2D API attempts to add a straight line from the current point to the start of the current sub-path. If the shape has already been closed or has only one point, this function does nothing.
dom-context-2d-closepath.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.closePath()

dom-context-2d-createimagedata.name: createImageData
dom-context-2d-createimagedata.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createImageData() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a new, blank ImageData object with the specified dimensions. All of the pixels in the new object are transparent black.
dom-context-2d-createimagedata.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.createImageData()

dom-context-2d-createlineargradient.name: createLinearGradient
dom-context-2d-createlineargradient.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createLinearGradient() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a gradient along the line connecting two given coordinates.
dom-context-2d-createlineargradient.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.createLinearGradient()

dom-context-2d-createpattern.name: createPattern
dom-context-2d-createpattern.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createPattern() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a pattern using the specified image and repetition. This method returns a CanvasPattern.
dom-context-2d-createpattern.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.createPattern()

dom-context-2d-createradialgradient.name: createRadialGradient
dom-context-2d-createradialgradient.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.createRadialGradient() method of the Canvas 2D API creates a radial gradient using the size and coordinates of two circles.
dom-context-2d-createradialgradient.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.createRadialGradient()

dom-context-2d-direction.name: direction
dom-context-2d-direction.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.direction property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current text direction used to draw text.
dom-context-2d-direction.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.direction

dom-context-2d-drawfocusifneeded.name: drawFocusIfNeeded
dom-context-2d-drawfocusifneeded.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawFocusIfNeeded() method of the Canvas 2D API draws a focus ring around the current or given path, if the specified element is focused.
dom-context-2d-drawfocusifneeded.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawFocusIfNeeded()

dom-context-2d-drawimage.name: drawImage
dom-context-2d-drawimage.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImage() method of the Canvas 2D API provides different ways to draw an image onto the canvas.
dom-context-2d-drawimage.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImage()

dom-context-2d-ellipse.name: ellipse
dom-context-2d-ellipse.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.ellipse() method of the Canvas 2D API adds an elliptical arc to the current sub-path.
dom-context-2d-ellipse.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.ellipse()

dom-context-2d-fill.name: fill
dom-context-2d-fill.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fill() method of the Canvas 2D API fills the current or given path with the current fillStyle.
dom-context-2d-fill.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.fill()

dom-context-2d-fillrect.name: fillRect
dom-context-2d-fillrect.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillRect() method of the Canvas 2D API draws a rectangle that is filled according to the current fillStyle.
dom-context-2d-fillrect.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillRect()

dom-context-2d-fillstyle.name: fillStyle
dom-context-2d-fillstyle.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillStyle property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color, gradient, or pattern to use inside shapes. The default style is #000 (black).
dom-context-2d-fillstyle.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillStyle

dom-context-2d-filltext.name: fillText
dom-context-2d-filltext.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D method fillText(), part of the Canvas 2D API, draws a text string at the specified coordinates, filling the string's characters with the current fillStyle. An optional parameter allows specifying a maximum width for the rendered text, which the user agent will achieve by condensing the text or by using a lower font size.
dom-context-2d-filltext.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillText()

filters.name: filter
filters.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.filter property of the Canvas 2D API provides filter effects such as blurring and grayscaling. It is similar to the CSS filter property and accepts the same values.
filters.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.filter

dom-context-2d-font.name: font
dom-context-2d-font.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.font property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current text style to use when drawing text. This string uses the same syntax as the CSS font specifier.
dom-context-2d-font.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.font

dom-context-2d-getimagedata.name: getImageData
dom-context-2d-getimagedata.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D method getImageData() of the Canvas 2D API returns an ImageData object representing the underlying pixel data for a specified portion of the canvas.

firefox.notes: Since Firefox 5, getImageData now correctly accepts rectangles that extend beyond the bounds of the canvas; pixels outside the canvas are returned as transparent black and now also returns at least one pixel's worth of image data if a rectangle smaller than one pixel is specified.

firefox_android.notes: Since Firefox 5, getImageData now correctly accepts rectangles that extend beyond the bounds of the canvas; pixels outside the canvas are returned as transparent black and now also returns at least one pixel's worth of image data if a rectangle smaller than one pixel is specified.

dom-context-2d-getimagedata.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.getImageData()

dom-context-2d-getlinedash.name: getLineDash
dom-context-2d-getlinedash.summary: The getLineDash() method of the Canvas 2D API's CanvasRenderingContext2D interface gets the current line dash pattern.
dom-context-2d-getlinedash.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.getLineDash()

dom-context-2d-gettransform.name: getTransform
dom-context-2d-gettransform.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.getTransform() method of the Canvas 2D API retrieves the current transformation matrix being applied to the context.
dom-context-2d-gettransform.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.getTransform()

dom-context-2d-globalalpha.name: globalAlpha
dom-context-2d-globalalpha.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalAlpha property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the alpha (transparency) value that is applied to shapes and images before they are drawn onto the canvas.
dom-context-2d-globalalpha.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalAlpha

dom-context-2d-globalcompositeoperation.name: globalCompositeOperation
dom-context-2d-globalcompositeoperation.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalCompositeOperation property of the Canvas 2D API sets the type of compositing operation to apply when drawing new shapes.
dom-context-2d-globalcompositeoperation.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.globalCompositeOperation

dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingenabled.name: imageSmoothingEnabled
dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingenabled.summary: The imageSmoothingEnabled property of the CanvasRenderingContext2D interface, part of the Canvas API, determines whether scaled images are smoothed (true, default) or not (false). On getting the imageSmoothingEnabled property, the last value it was set to is returned.
dom-context-2d-imagesmoothingenabled.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.imageSmoothingEnabled

imagesmoothingquality.name: imageSmoothingQuality
imagesmoothingquality.summary: The imageSmoothingQuality property of the CanvasRenderingContext2D interface, part of the Canvas API, lets you set the quality of image smoothing.
imagesmoothingquality.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.imageSmoothingQuality

dom-context-2d-ispointinpath.name: isPointInPath
dom-context-2d-ispointinpath.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.isPointInPath() method of the Canvas 2D API reports whether or not the specified point is contained in the current path.
dom-context-2d-ispointinpath.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.isPointInPath()

dom-context-2d-ispointinstroke.name: isPointInStroke
dom-context-2d-ispointinstroke.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.isPointInStroke() method of the Canvas 2D API reports whether or not the specified point is inside the area contained by the stroking of a path.
dom-context-2d-ispointinstroke.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.isPointInStroke()

dom-context-2d-linecap.name: lineCap
dom-context-2d-linecap.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineCap property of the Canvas 2D API determines the shape used to draw the end points of lines.
dom-context-2d-linecap.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineCap

dom-context-2d-linedashoffset.name: lineDashOffset
dom-context-2d-linedashoffset.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineDashOffset property of the Canvas 2D API sets the line dash offset, or "phase."
dom-context-2d-linedashoffset.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineDashOffset

dom-context-2d-linejoin.name: lineJoin
dom-context-2d-linejoin.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineJoin property of the Canvas 2D API determines the shape used to join two line segments where they meet.
dom-context-2d-linejoin.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineJoin

dom-context-2d-lineto.name: lineTo
dom-context-2d-lineto.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D method lineTo(), part of the Canvas 2D API, adds a straight line to the current sub-path by connecting the sub-path's last point to the specified (x, y) coordinates.
dom-context-2d-lineto.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineTo()

dom-context-2d-linewidth.name: lineWidth
dom-context-2d-linewidth.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineWidth property of the Canvas 2D API sets the thickness of lines.
dom-context-2d-linewidth.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.lineWidth

dom-context-2d-measuretext.name: measureText
dom-context-2d-measuretext.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.measureText() method returns a TextMetrics object that contains information about the measured text (such as its width, for example).
dom-context-2d-measuretext.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.measureText()

dom-context-2d-miterlimit.name: miterLimit
dom-context-2d-miterlimit.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.miterLimit property of the Canvas 2D API sets the miter limit ratio.
dom-context-2d-miterlimit.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.miterLimit

dom-context-2d-moveto.name: moveTo
dom-context-2d-moveto.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.moveTo() method of the Canvas 2D API begins a new sub-path at the point specified by the given (x, y) coordinates.
dom-context-2d-moveto.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.moveTo()

dom-context-2d-putimagedata.name: putImageData
dom-context-2d-putimagedata.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.putImageData() method of the Canvas 2D API paints data from the given ImageData object onto the canvas. If a dirty rectangle is provided, only the pixels from that rectangle are painted. This method is not affected by the canvas transformation matrix.
dom-context-2d-putimagedata.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.putImageData()

dom-context-2d-quadraticcurveto.name: quadraticCurveTo
dom-context-2d-quadraticcurveto.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.quadraticCurveTo() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a quadratic Bzier curve to the current sub-path. It requires two points: the first one is a control point and the second one is the end point. The starting point is the latest point in the current path, which can be changed using moveTo() before creating the quadratic Bzier curve.
dom-context-2d-quadraticcurveto.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.quadraticCurveTo()

dom-context-2d-rect.name: rect
dom-context-2d-rect.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.rect() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a rectangle to the current path.
dom-context-2d-rect.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.rect()

dom-context-2d-resettransform.name: resetTransform
dom-context-2d-resettransform.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.resetTransform() method of the Canvas 2D API resets the current transform to the identity matrix.
dom-context-2d-resettransform.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.resetTransform()

dom-context-2d-restore.name: restore
dom-context-2d-restore.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.restore() method of the Canvas 2D API restores the most recently saved canvas state by popping the top entry in the drawing state stack. If there is no saved state, this method does nothing.
dom-context-2d-restore.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.restore()

dom-context-2d-rotate.name: rotate
dom-context-2d-rotate.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.rotate() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a rotation to the transformation matrix.
dom-context-2d-rotate.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.rotate()

dom-context-2d-save.name: save
dom-context-2d-save.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.save() method of the Canvas 2D API saves the entire state of the canvas by pushing the current state onto a stack.
dom-context-2d-save.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.save()

dom-context-2d-scale.name: scale
dom-context-2d-scale.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.scale() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a scaling transformation to the canvas units horizontally and/or vertically.
dom-context-2d-scale.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.scale()

dom-context-2d-scrollpathintoview.name: scrollPathIntoView
dom-context-2d-scrollpathintoview.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.scrollPathIntoView() method of the Canvas 2D API scrolls the current or given path into view. It is similar to Element.scrollIntoView().
dom-context-2d-scrollpathintoview.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.scrollPathIntoView()

dom-context-2d-setlinedash.name: setLineDash
dom-context-2d-setlinedash.summary: The setLineDash() method of the Canvas 2D API's CanvasRenderingContext2D interface sets the line dash pattern used when stroking lines. It uses an array of values that specify alternating lengths of lines and gaps which describe the pattern.
dom-context-2d-setlinedash.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.setLineDash()

dom-context-2d-settransform.name: setTransform
dom-context-2d-settransform.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.setTransform() method of the Canvas 2D API resets (overrides) the current transformation to the identity matrix, and then invokes a transformation described by the arguments of this method. This lets you scale, rotate, translate (move), and skew the context.
dom-context-2d-settransform.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.setTransform()

dom-context-2d-shadowblur.name: shadowBlur
dom-context-2d-shadowblur.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowBlur property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the amount of blur applied to shadows. The default is 0 (no blur).
dom-context-2d-shadowblur.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowBlur

dom-context-2d-shadowcolor.name: shadowColor
dom-context-2d-shadowcolor.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowColor property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color of shadows.
dom-context-2d-shadowcolor.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowColor

dom-context-2d-shadowoffsetx.name: shadowOffsetX
dom-context-2d-shadowoffsetx.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowOffsetX property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the distance that shadows will be offset horizontally.
dom-context-2d-shadowoffsetx.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowOffsetX

dom-context-2d-shadowoffsety.name: shadowOffsetY
dom-context-2d-shadowoffsety.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowOffsetY property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the distance that shadows will be offset vertically.
dom-context-2d-shadowoffsety.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.shadowOffsetY

dom-context-2d-stroke.name: stroke
dom-context-2d-stroke.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.stroke() method of the Canvas 2D API strokes (outlines) the current or given path with the current stroke style.
dom-context-2d-stroke.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.stroke()

dom-context-2d-strokerect.name: strokeRect
dom-context-2d-strokerect.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.strokeRect() method of the Canvas 2D API draws a rectangle that is stroked (outlined) according to the current strokeStyle and other context settings.
dom-context-2d-strokerect.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.strokeRect()

dom-context-2d-strokestyle.name: strokeStyle
dom-context-2d-strokestyle.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.strokeStyle property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the color, gradient, or pattern to use for the strokes (outlines) around shapes. The default is #000 (black).
dom-context-2d-strokestyle.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.strokeStyle

dom-context-2d-stroketext.name: strokeText
dom-context-2d-stroketext.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D method strokeText(), part of the Canvas 2D API, strokes  that is, draws the outlines of  the characters of a text string at the specified coordinates. An optional parameter allows specifying a maximum width for the rendered text, which the user agent will achieve by condensing the text or by using a lower font size.
dom-context-2d-stroketext.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.strokeText()

dom-context-2d-textalign.name: textAlign
dom-context-2d-textalign.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.textAlign property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current text alignment used when drawing text.
dom-context-2d-textalign.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.textAlign

dom-context-2d-textbaseline.name: textBaseline
dom-context-2d-textbaseline.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline property of the Canvas 2D API specifies the current text baseline used when drawing text.
dom-context-2d-textbaseline.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseline

dom-context-2d-transform.name: transform
dom-context-2d-transform.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.transform() method of the Canvas 2D API multiplies the current transformation with the matrix described by the arguments of this method. This lets you scale, rotate, translate (move), and skew the context.
dom-context-2d-transform.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.transform()

dom-context-2d-translate.name: translate
dom-context-2d-translate.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D.translate() method of the Canvas 2D API adds a translation transformation to the current matrix.
dom-context-2d-translate.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D.translate()

2dcontext.name: CanvasRenderingContext2D
2dcontext.summary: The CanvasRenderingContext2D interface, part of the Canvas API, provides the 2D rendering context for the drawing surface of a <canvas> element. It is used for drawing shapes, text, images, and other objects.
2dcontext.title: CanvasRenderingContext2D

dom-parsing-and-serialization.name: DOMParser
dom-parsing-and-serialization.summary: The DOMParser interface provides the ability to parse XML or HTML source code from a string into a DOM Document.
dom-parsing-and-serialization.title: DOMParser

the-domstringlist-interface.name: DOMStringList
the-domstringlist-interface.summary: A type returned by some APIs which contains a list of DOMString (strings).
the-domstringlist-interface.title: DOMStringList

domstringmap.name: DOMStringMap
domstringmap.summary: The DOMStringMap interface is used for the HTMLElement.dataset attribute, to represent data for custom attributes added to elements.
domstringmap.title: DOMStringMap

dom-datatransfer.name: DataTransfer
dom-datatransfer.summary: The DataTransfer constructor creates a new DataTransfer object instance.
dom-datatransfer.title: DataTransfer()

dom-datatransfer-cleardata.name: clearData
dom-datatransfer-cleardata.summary: The DataTransfer.clearData() method removes the drag operation's drag data for the given type. If data for the given type does not exist, this method does nothing.
dom-datatransfer-cleardata.title: DataTransfer.clearData()

dom-datatransfer-dropeffect.name: dropEffect
dom-datatransfer-dropeffect.summary: The DataTransfer.dropEffect property controls the feedback (typically visual) the user is given during a drag and drop operation. It will affect which cursor is displayed while dragging. For example, when the user hovers over a target drop element, the browser's cursor may indicate which type of operation will occur.
dom-datatransfer-dropeffect.title: DataTransfer.dropEffect

dom-datatransfer-effectallowed.name: effectAllowed
dom-datatransfer-effectallowed.summary: The DataTransfer.effectAllowed property specifies the effect that is allowed for a drag operation. The copy operation is used to indicate that the data being dragged will be copied from its present location to the drop location. The move operation is used to indicate that the data being dragged will be moved, and the link operation is used to indicate that some form of relationship or connection will be created between the source and drop locations.
dom-datatransfer-effectallowed.title: DataTransfer.effectAllowed

dom-datatransfer-files.name: files
dom-datatransfer-files.summary: The DataTransfer.files property is a list of the files in the drag operation. If the operation includes no files, the list is empty.
dom-datatransfer-files.title: DataTransfer.files

dom-datatransfer-getdata.name: getData
dom-datatransfer-getdata.summary: The DataTransfer.getData() method retrieves drag data (as a DOMString) for the specified type. If the drag operation does not include data, this method returns an empty string.
dom-datatransfer-getdata.title: DataTransfer.getData()

dom-datatransfer-items.name: items
dom-datatransfer-items.summary: The read-only DataTransfer property items property is a list of the data transfer items in a drag operation. The list includes one item for each item in the operation and if the operation had no items, the list is empty.
dom-datatransfer-items.title: DataTransfer.items

dom-datatransfer-setdata.name: setData
dom-datatransfer-setdata.summary: The DataTransfer.setData() method sets the drag operation's drag data to the specified data and type. If data for the given type does not exist, it is added at the end of the drag data store, such that the last item in the types list will be the new type. If data for the given type already exists, the existing data is replaced in the same position. That is, the order of the types list is not changed when replacing data of the same type.
dom-datatransfer-setdata.title: DataTransfer.setData()

dom-datatransfer-setdragimage.name: setDragImage
dom-datatransfer-setdragimage.summary: When a drag occurs, a translucent image is generated from the drag target (the element the dragstart event is fired at), and follows the mouse pointer during the drag. This image is created automatically, so you do not need to create it yourself. However, if a custom image is desired, the DataTransfer.setDragImage() method can be used to set the custom image to be used. The image will typically be an <image> element but it can also be a <canvas> or any other visible element.
dom-datatransfer-setdragimage.title: DataTransfer.setDragImage()

dom-datatransfer-types.name: types
dom-datatransfer-types.summary: The DataTransfer.types read-only property returns an array of the drag data formats (as strings) that were set in the dragstart event. The order of the formats is the same order as the data included in the drag operation.

notes: The property returns a DOMStringList.
Text is returned instead of text/plain

opera.notes: As of Opera 12, Text is returned instead of text/plain

dom-datatransfer-types.title: DataTransfer.types

datatransfer.name: DataTransfer
datatransfer.summary: The DataTransfer object is used to hold the data that is being dragged during a drag and drop operation. It may hold one or more data items, each of one or more data types. For more information about drag and drop, see HTML Drag and Drop API.

firefox.notes: As of Firefox 52, the DataTransfer.types property returns a frozen array of DOMStrings as per spec, rather than a DOMStringList.

firefox_android.notes: As of Firefox 52, the DataTransfer.types property returns a frozen array of DOMStrings as per spec, rather than a DOMStringList.

datatransfer.title: DataTransfer

dom-datatransferitem-getasfile.name: getAsFile
dom-datatransferitem-getasfile.summary: If the item is a file, the DataTransferItem.getAsFile() method returns the drag data item's File object. If the item is not a file, this method returns null.
dom-datatransferitem-getasfile.title: DataTransferItem.getAsFile()

dom-datatransferitem-getasstring.name: getAsString
dom-datatransferitem-getasstring.summary: The DataTransferItem.getAsString() method invokes the given callback with the drag data item's string data as the argument if the item's kind is a Plain unicode string (i.e. kind is string).
dom-datatransferitem-getasstring.title: DataTransferItem.getAsString()

dom-datatransferitem-kind.name: kind
dom-datatransferitem-kind.summary: The read-only DataTransferItem.kind property returns a DataTransferItem representing the drag data item kind: some text or some file.
dom-datatransferitem-kind.title: DataTransferItem.kind

dom-datatransferitem-type.name: type
dom-datatransferitem-type.summary: The read-only DataTransferItem.type property returns the type (format) of the DataTransferItem object representing the drag data item. The type is a Unicode string generally given by a MIME type, although a MIME type is not required.
dom-datatransferitem-type.title: DataTransferItem.type

datatransferitem.name: DataTransferItem
datatransferitem.summary: The DataTransferItem object represents one drag data item. During a drag operation, each drag event has a dataTransfer property which contains a list of drag data items. Each item in the list is a DataTransferItem object.
datatransferitem.title: DataTransferItem

the-datatransferitemlist-interface.name: DataTransferItem
the-datatransferitemlist-interface.summary: The DataTransferItem() getter method implements support for accessing items in the DataTransferItemList using array-style syntax (that is DataTransferItem[index]).
the-datatransferitemlist-interface.title: DataTransferItemList.DataTransferItem()

dom-datatransferitemlist-add.name: add
dom-datatransferitemlist-add.summary: The DataTransferItemList.add() method creates a new DataTransferItem using the specified data and adds it to the drag data list. The item may be a File or a string of a given type. If the item is successfully added to the list, the newly-created DataTransferItem object is returned.
dom-datatransferitemlist-add.title: DataTransferItemList.add()

dom-datatransferitemlist-clear.name: clear
dom-datatransferitemlist-clear.summary: The DataTransferItemList method clear() removes all DataTransferItem objects from the drag data items list, leaving the list empty.
dom-datatransferitemlist-clear.title: DataTransferItemList.clear()

dom-datatransferitemlist-length.name: length
dom-datatransferitemlist-length.summary: The read-only length property of the DataTransferItemList interface returns the number of items currently in the drag item list.
dom-datatransferitemlist-length.title: DataTransferItemList.length

datatransferitemlist.name: DataTransferItemList
datatransferitemlist.summary: The DataTransferItemList object is a list of DataTransferItem objects representing items being dragged. During a drag operation, each DragEvent has a dataTransfer property and that property is a DataTransferItemList.
datatransferitemlist.title: DataTransferItemList

dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-close.name: close
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-close.summary: The close() method of the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope interface discards any tasks queued in the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope's event loop, effectively closing this particular scope.
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-close.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.close()

dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-name.name: name
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-name.summary: The name read-only property of the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope interface returns the name that the Worker was (optionally) given when it was created. This is the name that the Worker() constructor can pass to get a reference to the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-name.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.name

handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.name: onmessage
handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.summary: The onmessage property of the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope interface represents an EventHandler to be called when the message event occurs and bubbles through the Worker  i.e. when a message is sent to the worker using the Worker.postMessage method.
handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.onmessage

handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.name: onmessageerror
handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.summary: The onmessageerror event handler of the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope interface is an EventListener, called whenever an MessageEvent of type messageerror is fired on the workerthat is, when it receives a message that cannot be deserialized.
handler-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-onmes.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.onmessageerror

dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-postmessa.name: postMessage
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-postmessa.summary: The postMessage() method of the DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope interface sends a message to the main thread that spawned it. This accepts a single parameter, which is the data to send to the worker. The data may be any value or JavaScript object handled by the structured clone algorithm, which includes cyclical references.
dom-dedicatedworkerglobalscope-postmessa.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.postMessage()

dedicatedworkerglobalscope.name: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope
dedicatedworkerglobalscope.summary: The DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object (the Worker global scope) is accessible through the self keyword. Some additional global functions, namespaces objects, and constructors, not typically associated with the worker global scope, but available on it, are listed in the JavaScript Reference. See also: Functions available to workers.
dedicatedworkerglobalscope.title: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope

stop-parsing.name: DOMContentLoaded_event
stop-parsing.summary: The DOMContentLoaded event fires when the initial HTML document has been completely loaded and parsed, without waiting for stylesheets, images, and subframes to finish loading.
stop-parsing.title: Document: DOMContentLoaded event

dom-document-body.name: body
dom-document-body.summary: The Document.body property represents the <body> or <frameset> node of the current document, or null if no such element exists.

firefox.notes: The body property was implemented on the HTMLDocument interface in Firefox for a long time, hence document.body would not return the <body> element if the document's Content-Type was not set to text/html or application/xhtml+xml (or if it came from DOMParser.parseFromString without the text/html type being used). This has been fixed in Firefox 60.

This has been fixed in Firefox 60.

dom-document-currentscript.summary: The Document.currentScript property returns the <script> element whose script is currently being processed and isn't a JavaScript module. (For modules use import.meta instead.)
dom-document-currentscript.title: Document.currentScript

dom-document-defaultview.name: defaultView
dom-document-defaultview.summary: In browsers, document.defaultView returns the window object associated with a document, or null if none is available.
dom-document-defaultview.title: Document.defaultView

making-entire-documents-editable:-the-de.name: designMode
making-entire-documents-editable:-the-de.summary: document.designMode controls whether the entire document is editable. Valid values are "on" and "off". According to the specification, this property is meant to default to "off". Firefox follows this standard. The earlier versions of Chrome and IE default to "inherit". Starting in Chrome 43, the default is "off" and "inherit" is no longer supported. In IE6-10, the value is capitalized.
making-entire-documents-editable:-the-de.title: Document.designMode

dom-document-dir.name: dir
dom-document-dir.summary: The Document.dir property is a DOMString representing the directionality of the text of the document, whether left to right (default) or right to left. Possible values are 'rtl', right to left, and 'ltr', left to right.

relaxing-the-same-origin-restriction.name: domain
relaxing-the-same-origin-restriction.summary: The domain property of the Document interface gets/sets the domain portion of the origin of the current document, as used by the same-origin policy.

firefox.notes: From Firefox 62, if the domain cannot be identified, domain returns an empty string instead of null. See bug 819475.

firefox_android.notes: From Firefox 62, if the domain cannot be identified, domain returns an empty string instead of null. See bug 819475.

relaxing-the-same-origin-restriction.title: Document.domain

dndevents.name: drag_event
dndevents.summary: The drag event is fired every few hundred milliseconds as an element or text selection is being dragged by the user.

firefox.notes: Firefox doesn't set the mouse coordinates during the drag event. See bug 505521.

dndevents.title: Document: drag event

dndevents.name: dragend_event
dndevents.summary: The dragend event is fired when a drag operation is being ended (by releasing a mouse button or hitting the escape key).

chrome.notes: Prior to Chrome 72, the dragend event was not dispatched if an iframe (not necessarily the source target) is involved in a DOM operation. See issue 737691 for more details.

notes: Firefox doesn't set the mouse coordinates during the drag event. See bug 505521.
In Firefox, dragend is not dispatched if the source node is moved or removed during the drag (e.g. on drop or dragover). See bug 460801 for details.

edge_blink.notes: Prior to Chrome 72, the dragend event was not dispatched if an iframe (not necessarily the source target) is involved in a DOM operation. See issue 737691 for more details.

dndevents.title: Document: dragend event

dndevents.name: dragenter_event
dndevents.summary: The dragenter event is fired when a dragged element or text selection enters a valid drop target.

firefox.notes: In Firefox, the dragenter event is fired twice when the dropzone is parent of draggable or draggable itself. See bug 804036 for details.

dndevents.title: Document: dragenter event

dndevents.name: dragleave_event
dndevents.summary: The dragleave event is fired when a dragged element or text selection leaves a valid drop target.
dndevents.title: Document: dragleave event

dndevents.name: dragover_event
dndevents.summary: The dragover event is fired when an element or text selection is being dragged over a valid drop target (every few hundred milliseconds).
dndevents.title: Document: dragover event

dndevents.name: dragstart_event
dndevents.summary: The dragstart event is fired when the user starts dragging an element or text selection.
dndevents.title: Document: dragstart event

dndevents.name: drop_event
dndevents.summary: The drop event is fired when an element or text selection is dropped on a valid drop target.
dndevents.title: Document: drop event

dom-document-embeds.name: embeds
dom-document-embeds.summary: The embeds read-only property of the Document interface returns a list of the embedded <object> elements within the current document.

dom-iframe-contentdocument.name: contentDocument
dom-iframe-contentdocument.summary: If the iframe and the iframe's parent document are Same Origin, returns a Document (that is, the active document in the inline frame's nested browsing context), else returns null.
dom-iframe-contentdocument.title: contentDocument

dom-iframe-contentwindow.name: contentWindow
dom-iframe-contentwindow.summary: The contentWindow property returns the Window object of an HTMLIFrameElement. You can use this Window object to access the iframe's document and its internal DOM. This attribute is read-only, but its properties can be manipulated like the global Window object.
dom-iframe-contentwindow.title: HTMLIFrameElement.contentWindow

dom-iframe-referrerpolicy.name: referrerPolicy
dom-iframe-referrerpolicy.summary: The HTMLIFrameElement.referrerPolicy property reflects the HTML referrerpolicy attribute of the <iframe> element defining which referrer is sent when fetching the resource.
dom-iframe-referrerpolicy.title: HTMLIFrameElement.referrerPolicy

dom-iframe-src.name: src
dom-iframe-src.summary: The HTMLIFrameElement.src property reflects the HTML referrerpolicy attribute of the <iframe> element defining which referrer is sent when fetching the resource.
dom-iframe-src.title: HTMLIFrameElement.src

htmliframeelement.name: HTMLIFrameElement
htmliframeelement.summary: The HTMLIFrameElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of inline frame elements.
htmliframeelement.title: HTMLIFrameElement

dom-image.name: Image
dom-image.summary: The Image() constructor creates a new HTMLImageElement instance. It is functionally equivalent to document.createElement('img').
dom-image.title: Image()

attr-img-align.name: align
attr-img-align.summary: The obsolete align property of the HTMLImageElement interface is a string which indicates how to position the image relative to its container.
attr-img-align.title: HTMLImageElement.align

dom-img-alt.name: alt
dom-img-alt.summary: The HTMLImageElement property alt provides fallback (alternate) text to display when the image specified by the element is not loaded.
dom-img-alt.title: HTMLImageElement.alt

dom-img-border.name: border
dom-img-border.summary: The obsolete HTMLImageElement property border specifies the number of pixels thick the border surrounding the image should be. A value of 0, the default, indicates that no border should be drawn.
dom-img-border.title: HTMLImageElement.border

dom-img-complete.name: complete
dom-img-complete.summary: The read-only HTMLImageElement interface's complete attribute is a Boolean value which indicates whether or not the image has completely loaded.

ie.notes: IE reports false for broken images.

dom-img-complete.title: HTMLImageElement.complete

dom-img-crossorigin.name: crossOrigin
dom-img-crossorigin.summary: The HTMLImageElement interface's crossOrigin attribute is a string which specifies the Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) setting to use when retrieving the image.
dom-img-crossorigin.title: HTMLImageElement.crossOrigin

dom-img-currentsrc.name: currentSrc
dom-img-currentsrc.summary: The read-only HTMLImageElement property currentSrc indicates the URL of the image which is currently presented in the element it represents.
dom-img-currentsrc.title: HTMLImageElement.currentSrc

dom-img-decode.name: decode
dom-img-decode.summary: The decode() method of the HTMLImageElement interface returns a Promise that resolves when the image is decoded and it is safe to append the image to the DOM.
dom-img-decode.title: HTMLImageElement.decode()

dom-img-decode.name: decode
dom-img-decode.summary: The decode() method of the SVGImageElement interface initiates asynchronous decoding of an image, returning a Promise that
dom-img-decode.title: SVGImageElement.decode

dom-img-decoding.name: decoding
dom-img-decoding.summary: The decoding property of the HTMLImageElement interface represents a hint given to the browser on how it should decode the image.
dom-img-decoding.title: HTMLImageElement.decoding

dom-img-height.name: height
dom-img-height.summary: The height property of the HTMLImageElement interface indicates the height at which the image is drawn, in CSS pixels if the image is being drawn or rendered to any visual medium such as the screen or a printer; otherwise, it's the natural, pixel density corrected height of the image.
dom-img-height.title: HTMLImageElement.height

attr-img-hspace.name: hspace
attr-img-hspace.summary: The obsolete hspace property of the HTMLImageElement interface specifies the number of pixels of empty space to leave empty on the left and right sides of the element when laying out the page.
attr-img-hspace.title: HTMLImageElement.hspace

dom-img-ismap.name: isMap
dom-img-ismap.summary: The HTMLImageElement proeprty isMap is a Boolean value which indicates that the image is to be used by a server-side image map. This may only be used on images located within an <a> element.
dom-img-ismap.title: HTMLImageElement.isMap

attr-img-name.name: name
attr-img-name.summary: The HTMLImageElement interface's deprecated name property specifies a name for the element. This has been replaced by the id property available on all elements.
attr-img-name.title: HTMLImageElement.name

dom-img-naturalheight.name: naturalHeight
dom-img-naturalheight.summary: The HTMLImageElement interface's naturalHeight property is a read-only value which returns the intrinsic (natural), density-corrected height of the image in CSS pixels.
dom-img-naturalheight.title: HTMLImageElement.naturalHeight

dom-img-naturalwidth.name: naturalWidth
dom-img-naturalwidth.summary: The HTMLImageElement interface's read-only naturalWidth property returns the intrinsic (natural), density-corrected width of the image in CSS pixels.
dom-img-naturalwidth.title: HTMLImageElement.naturalWidth

dom-img-sizes.name: sizes
dom-img-sizes.summary: The HTMLImageElement property sizes allows you to specify the layout width of the image for each of a list of media conditions. This provides the ability to automatically select among different imageseven images of different orientations or aspect ratiosas the document state changes to match different media conditions.
dom-img-sizes.title: HTMLImageElement.sizes

dom-img-src.name: src
dom-img-src.summary: The HTMLImageElement property src, which reflects the HTML src attribute, specifies the image to display in the element.
dom-img-src.title: HTMLImageElement.src

dom-img-srcset.name: srcset
dom-img-srcset.summary: The HTMLImageElement property srcset is a string which identifies one or more image candidate strings, separated using commas (,) each specifying image resources to use under given circumstances.
dom-img-srcset.title: HTMLImageElement.srcset

dom-img-usemap.name: useMap
dom-img-usemap.summary: The useMap property on the HTMLImageElement interface reflects the value of the HTML usemap attribute, which is a string providing the name of the client-side image map to apply to the image.
dom-img-usemap.title: HTMLImageElement.useMap

dom-img-vspace.name: vspace
dom-img-vspace.summary: The obsolete vspace property of the HTMLImageElement interface specifies the number of pixels of empty space to leave empty on the top and bottom of the element when laying out the page.
dom-img-vspace.title: HTMLImageElement.vspace

dom-img-width.name: width
dom-img-width.summary: The width property of the HTMLImageElement interface indicates the width at which an image is drawn in CSS pixels if it's being drawn or rendered to any visual medium such as a screen or printer. Otherwise, it's the natural, pixel density-corrected width of the image.
dom-img-width.title: HTMLImageElement.width

htmlimageelement.name: HTMLImageElement
htmlimageelement.summary: The HTMLImageElement interface represents an HTML element, providing the properties and methods used to manipulate image elements.
htmlimageelement.title: HTMLImageElement

the-constraint-validation-api.name: invalid_event
the-constraint-validation-api.summary: The invalid event fires when a submittable element has been checked for validity and doesn't satisfy its constraints.
the-constraint-validation-api.title: HTMLInputElement: invalid event

attr-input-multiple.name: multiple
attr-input-multiple.summary: The HTMLInputElement.multiple property indicates if an input can have more than one value. Firefox currently only supports multiple for <input type="file">.
attr-input-multiple.title: HTMLInputElement.multiple

attr-input-multiple.name: input#attr-multiple
attr-input-multiple.summary: The HTML <input> element is used to create interactive controls for web-based forms in order to accept data from the user; a wide variety of types of input data and control widgets are available, depending on the device and user agent.
attr-input-multiple.title: <input>: The Input (Form Input) element

dom-textarea/input-setrangetext.name: setRangeText
dom-textarea/input-setrangetext.summary: The HTMLInputElement.setRangeText() method replaces a range of text in an <input> or <textarea> element with a new string.
dom-textarea/input-setrangetext.title: HTMLInputElement.setRangeText()

dom-textarea/input-setselectionrange.name: setSelectionRange
dom-textarea/input-setselectionrange.summary: The HTMLInputElement.setSelectionRange() method sets the start and end positions of the current text selection in an <input> or <textarea> element.
dom-textarea/input-setselectionrange.title: HTMLInputElement.setSelectionRange()

dom-input-stepdown.name: stepDown
dom-input-stepdown.summary: The HTMLInputElement.stepDown([n]) method decrements the value of a numeric type of  <input> element by the value of the step attribute or up to n multiples of the step attribute if a number is passed as the parameter.

firefox.notes: Experimental, and without specific UI. There are still differences with the latest spec: bug 835773.

dom-input-stepdown.title: HTMLInputElement.stepDown()

dom-input-stepup.name: stepUp
dom-input-stepup.summary: The HTMLInputElement.stepUp() method increments the value of a numeric type of  <input> element by the value of the step attribute, or the default step value if the step attribute is not explicitly set. The method, when invoked, increments the value by (step * n), where n defaults to 1 if not specified, and step defaults to the default value for step if not specified.

firefox.notes: Experimental, and without specific UI. There are still differences with the latest spec: bug 835773.

dom-input-stepup.title: HTMLInputElement.stepUp()

htmlinputelement.name: HTMLInputElement
htmlinputelement.summary: The HTMLInputElement interface provides special properties and methods for manipulating the options, layout, and presentation of <input> elements.
htmlinputelement.title: HTMLInputElement

htmllielement.name: HTMLLIElement
htmllielement.summary: The HTMLLIElement interface exposes specific properties and methods (beyond those defined by regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating list elements.

firefox.notes: Prior to Firefox 10, Gecko incorrectly reflected negative value attributes to 0.

firefox_android.notes: Prior to Firefox 10, Gecko incorrectly reflected negative value attributes to 0.

htmllielement.title: HTMLLIElement

dom-label-control.name: control
dom-label-control.summary: The read-only HTMLLabelElement.control property returns a reference to the control (in the form of an object of type HTMLElement or one of its derivatives) with which the <label> element is associated, or null if the label isn't associated with a control.
dom-label-control.title: HTMLLabelElement.control

dom-label-form.name: form
dom-label-form.summary: The read-only HTMLLabelElement.form property returns an HTMLFormElement object which represents the form of which the label's associated control is a part, or null if there is either no associated control, or if that control isn't in a form.
dom-label-form.title: HTMLLabelElement.form

dom-label-htmlfor.name: htmlFor
dom-label-htmlfor.summary: The HTMLLabelElement.htmlFor property reflects the value of the for content property. That means that this script-accessible property is used to set and read the value of the content property for, which is the ID of the label's associated control element.
dom-label-htmlfor.title: HTMLLabelElement.htmlFor

htmllabelelement.name: HTMLLabelElement
htmllabelelement.summary: The HTMLLabelElement interface gives access to properties specific to <label> elements. It inherits methods and properties from the base HTMLElement interface.
htmllabelelement.title: HTMLLabelElement

htmllegendelement.name: HTMLLegendElement
htmllegendelement.summary: The HTMLLegendElement is an interface allowing to access properties of the <legend> elements. It inherits properties and methods from the HTMLElement interface.
htmllegendelement.title: HTMLLegendElement

attr-link-rel.name: rel
attr-link-rel.summary: The HTMLLinkElement.rel property reflects the rel attribute. It is a DOMString containing a space-separated list of link types indicating the relationship between the resource represented by the <link> element and the current document.
attr-link-rel.title: HTMLLinkElement.rel

dom-link-rellist.name: relList
dom-link-rellist.summary: The HTMLLinkElement.relList read-only property reflects the rel attribute. It is a live DOMTokenList containing the set of link types indicating the relationship between the resource represented by the <link> element and the current document.
dom-link-rellist.title: HTMLLinkElement.relList

htmllinkelement.name: HTMLLinkElement
htmllinkelement.summary: The HTMLLinkElement interface represents reference information for external resources and the relationship of those resources to a document and vice-versa (corresponds to <link> element; not to be confused with <a>, which is represented by HTMLAnchorElement). This object inherits all of the properties and methods of the HTMLElement interface.
htmllinkelement.title: HTMLLinkElement

htmlmapelement.name: HTMLMapElement
htmlmapelement.summary: The HTMLMapElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular object HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of map elements.
htmlmapelement.title: HTMLMapElement

event-media-abort.name: abort_event
event-media-abort.summary: The abort event is fired when the resource was not fully loaded, but not as the result of an error.
event-media-abort.title: HTMLMediaElement: abort event

dom-media-audiotracks.name: audioTracks
dom-media-audiotracks.summary: The read-only audioTracks property on HTMLMediaElement objects returns an AudioTrackList object listing all of the  AudioTrack objects representing the media element's audio tracks.
dom-media-audiotracks.title: HTMLMediaElement.audioTracks

dom-media-autoplay.name: autoplay
dom-media-autoplay.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.autoplay property reflects the autoplay HTML attribute, indicating whether playback should automatically begin as soon as enough media is available to do so without interruption.
dom-media-autoplay.title: HTMLMediaElement.autoplay

media-elements.name: buffered
media-elements.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.buffered read-only property returns a new TimeRanges object that indicates the ranges of the media source that the browser has buffered (if any) at the moment the buffered property is accessed.
media-elements.title: HTMLMediaElement.buffered

event-media-canplay.name: canplay_event
event-media-canplay.summary: The canplay event is fired when the user agent can play the media, but estimates that not enough data has been loaded to play the media up to its end without having to stop for further buffering of content.
event-media-canplay.title: HTMLMediaElement: canplay event

event-media-canplaythrough.name: canplaythrough_event
event-media-canplaythrough.summary: The canplaythrough event is fired when the user agent can play the media, and estimates that enough data has been loaded to play the media up to its end without having to stop for further buffering of content.
event-media-canplaythrough.title: HTMLMediaElement: canplaythrough event

dom-navigator-canplaytype.name: canPlayType
dom-navigator-canplaytype.summary: The HTMLMediaElement method canPlayType() reports how likely it is that the current browser will be able to play media of a given MIME type.

firefox.notes: Prior to Firefox 28, canPlayType() returned probably when asked about WebM audio or video files without the codecs parameter. Since multiple codecs are supported, this is not enough information to determine if a file can be played, so maybe is now correctly returned.

dom-navigator-canplaytype.title: HTMLMediaElement.canPlayType()

dom-media-controls.name: controls
dom-media-controls.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.controls property reflects the controls HTML attribute, which controls whether user interface controls for playing the media item will be displayed.
dom-media-controls.title: HTMLMediaElement.controls

attr-media-crossorigin.name: crossOrigin
attr-media-crossorigin.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.crossOrigin property is the CORS setting for this image element. See CORS settings attributes for details.
attr-media-crossorigin.title: HTMLMediaElement.crossOrigin

dom-media-currentsrc.name: currentSrc
dom-media-currentsrc.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.currentSrc property contains the absolute URL of the chosen media resource. This could happen, for example, if the web server selects a media file based on the resolution of the user's display. The value is an empty string if the networkState property is EMPTY.
dom-media-currentsrc.title: HTMLMediaElement.currentSrc

dom-media-currenttime.name: currentTime
dom-media-currenttime.summary: The HTMLMediaElement interface's currentTime property specifies the current playback time in seconds.
dom-media-currenttime.title: HTMLMediaElement.currentTime

dom-media-defaultmuted.name: defaultMuted
dom-media-defaultmuted.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.defaultMuted property reflects the muted HTML attribute, which indicates whether the media element's audio output should be muted by default. This property has no dynamic effect. To mute and unmute the audio output, use the muted property.
dom-media-defaultmuted.title: HTMLMediaElement.defaultMuted

dom-media-defaultplaybackrate.name: defaultPlaybackRate
dom-media-defaultplaybackrate.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.defaultPlaybackRate property indicates the default playback rate for the media.
dom-media-defaultplaybackrate.title: HTMLMediaElement.defaultPlaybackRate

dom-media-duration.name: duration
dom-media-duration.summary: The read-only HTMLMediaElement property duration indicates the length of the element's media in seconds.
dom-media-duration.title: HTMLMediaElement.duration

event-media-durationchange.name: durationchange_event
event-media-durationchange.summary: The durationchange event is fired when the duration attribute has been updated.
event-media-durationchange.title: HTMLMediaElement: durationchange event

event-media-emptied.name: emptied_event
event-media-emptied.summary: The emptied event is fired when the media has become empty; for example, this event is sent if the media has already been loaded (or partially loaded), and the load() method is called to reload it.
event-media-emptied.title: HTMLMediaElement: emptied event

dom-media-ended.name: ended
dom-media-ended.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.ended indicates whether the media element has ended playback.
dom-media-ended.title: HTMLMediaElement.ended

event-media-ended.name: ended_event
event-media-ended.summary: The ended event is fired when playback or streaming has stopped because the end of the media was reached or because no further data is available.
event-media-ended.title: HTMLMediaElement: ended event

dom-media-error.name: error
dom-media-error.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.error is the MediaError object for the most recent error, or null if there has not been an error. When an error event is received by the element, you can determine details about what happened by examining this object.
dom-media-error.title: HTMLMediaElement.error

event-media-error.name: error_event
event-media-error.summary: The error event is fired when the resource could not be loaded due to an error (for example, a network connectivity problem).
event-media-error.title: HTMLMediaElement: error event

dom-media-fastseek.name: fastSeek
dom-media-fastseek.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.fastSeek() method quickly seeks the media to the new time with precision tradeoff.
dom-media-fastseek.title: HTMLMediaElement.fastSeek()

dom-media-load.name: load
dom-media-load.summary: The HTMLMediaElement method load() resets the media element to its initial state and begins the process of selecting a media source and loading the media in preparation for playback to begin at the beginning.
dom-media-load.title: HTMLMediaElement.load()

event-media-loadeddata.name: loadeddata_event
event-media-loadeddata.summary: The loadeddata event is fired when the frame at the current playback position of the media has finished loading; often the first frame.
event-media-loadeddata.title: HTMLMediaElement: loadeddata event

event-media-loadedmetadata.name: loadedmetadata_event
event-media-loadedmetadata.summary: The loadedmetadata event is fired when the metadata has been loaded.
event-media-loadedmetadata.title: HTMLMediaElement: loadedmetadata event

event-media-loadstart.name: loadstart_event
event-media-loadstart.summary: The loadstart event is fired when the browser has started to load a resource.
event-media-loadstart.title: HTMLMediaElement: loadstart event

dom-media-loop.name: loop
dom-media-loop.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.loop property reflects the loop HTML attribute, which controls whether the media element should start over when it reaches the end.
dom-media-loop.title: HTMLMediaElement.loop

dom-media-muted.name: muted
dom-media-muted.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.muted indicates whether the media element muted.
dom-media-muted.title: HTMLMediaElement.muted

dom-media-networkstate.name: networkState
dom-media-networkstate.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.networkState property indicates the current state of the fetching of media over the network.

firefox.notes: The NETWORK_LOADED state was removed to align with the HTML spec in Firefox 4.

dom-media-networkstate.title: HTMLMediaElement.networkState

dom-media-pause.name: pause
dom-media-pause.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.pause() method will pause playback of the media, if the media is already in a paused state this method will have no effect.
dom-media-pause.title: HTMLMediaElement.pause()

event-media-pause.name: pause_event
event-media-pause.summary: The pause event is sent when a request to pause an activity is handled and the activity has entered its paused state, most commonly after the media has been paused through a call to the element's pause() method.
event-media-pause.title: HTMLMediaElement: pause event

dom-media-paused.name: paused
dom-media-paused.summary: The read-only HTMLMediaElement.paused property tells whether the media element is paused.
dom-media-paused.title: HTMLMediaElement.paused

dom-media-play.name: play
dom-media-play.summary: The HTMLMediaElement play() method attempts to begin playback of the media. It returns a Promise which is resolved when playback has been successfully started.
dom-media-play.title: HTMLMediaElement.play()

event-media-play.name: play_event
event-media-play.summary: The play event is fired when the paused property is changed from true to false, as a result of the play method, or the autoplay attribute.
event-media-play.title: HTMLMediaElement: play event

dom-media-playbackrate.name: playbackRate
dom-media-playbackrate.summary: The HTMLMediaElement.playbackRate property sets the rate at which the media is being played back. This is used to implement user controls for fast forward, slow motion, and so forth. The normal playback rate is multiplied by this value to obtain the current rate, so a value of 1.0 indicates normal speed.
dom-media-playbackrate.title: HTMLMediaElement.playbackRate

event-media-playing.name: playing_event
event-media-playing.summary: The playing event is fired when playback is ready to start after having been paused or delayed due to lack of data.
event-media-playing.title: HTMLMediaElement: playing event

event-media-progress.name: progress_event
event-media-progress.summary: The progress event is fired periodically as the browser loads a resource.
event-media-progress.title: HTMLMediaElement: progress event

event-media-ratechange.name: ratechange_event
event-media-ratechange.summary: The ratechange event is fired when the playback rate has changed.

htmlmetaelement.name: HTMLMetaElement

htmlmodelement.name: HTMLModElement

htmlolistelement.name: HTMLOListElement

dom-cva-checkvalidity.name: checkValidity

dom-cva-checkvalidity.name: checkValidity
dom-cva-checkvalidity.summary: The HTMLSelectElement.checkValidity() method checks whether the element has any constraints and whether it satisfies them. If the element fails its constraints, the browser fires a cancelable invalid event at the element, and then returns false.
dom-cva-checkvalidity.title: HTMLSelectElement.checkValidity()

dom-object-contentwindow.name: contentDocument
dom-object-contentwindow.summary: The contentDocument read-only property of the HTMLObjectElement interface Returns a Document representing the active document of the object element's nested browsing context, if any; otherwise null.
dom-object-contentwindow.title: HTMLObjectElement.contentDocument

dom-object-contentwindow.name: contentWindow

dom-object-data.name: data

dom-object-data.title: HTMLObjectElement.data

dom-fae-form.name: form
dom-fae-form.summary: The form read-only property of the HTMLObjectElement interface Retuns a HTMLFormElement representing the object element's form owner, or null if there isn't one.
dom-fae-form.title: HTMLObjectElement.form

dom-fae-form.name: form
dom-fae-form.summary: The HTMLSelectElement.form read-only property returns a HTMLFormElement representing the form that this element is associated with. If the element is not associated with of a <form> element, then it returns null.
dom-fae-form.title: HTMLSelectElement.form

dom-dim-height.name: height
dom-dim-height.summary: The height property of the HTMLObjectElement interface Returns a DOMString that reflects the height HTML attribute, specifying the displayed height of the resource in CSS pixels.
dom-dim-height.title: HTMLObjectElement.height

dom-object-name.name: name
dom-object-name.summary: The name property of the HTMLObjectElement interface returns a DOMString that reflects the name HTML attribute, specifying the name of the browsing context.

dom-cva-setcustomvalidity.name: setCustomValidity

dom-cva-setcustomvalidity.summary: The HTMLSelectElement.setCustomValidity() method sets the custom validity message for the selection element to the specified message. Use the empty string to indicate that the element does not have a custom validity error.

dom-object-type.name: type
dom-object-type.summary: The type property of the HTMLObjectElement interface returns a DOMString that reflects the type HTML attribute, specifying the MIME type of the resource.
dom-object-type.title: HTMLObjectElement.type

dom-cva-validity.name: validity
